de.saxsys.mvvmfx

Class FluentViewLoader.FxmlViewStep<ViewType extends FxmlView<? extends ViewModelType>,ViewModelType extends ViewModel>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.saxsys.mvvmfx.FluentViewLoader.FxmlViewStep<ViewType,ViewModelType>
  • Type Parameters:
    ViewType - the generic type of the View that should be loaded. This type has to implement FxmlView.
    ViewModelType - the generic type of the ViewModel. This type has to implement ViewModel.
    Enclosing class:
    FluentViewLoader

    public static class FluentViewLoader.FxmlViewStep<ViewType extends FxmlView<? extends ViewModelType>,ViewModelType extends ViewModel>
extends Object
    This class is the builder step to load a fxml based view. It is accessed from the FluentViewLoader with the method FluentViewLoader.fxmlView(Class).

    • Method Detail

      • resourceBundle

        public FluentViewLoader.FxmlViewStep<ViewType,ViewModelType> resourceBundle(ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
        Provide a ResourceBundle that is used while loading this view. Note: It is possible to provide a global application-wide resourceBundle via MvvmFX.setGlobalResourceBundle(ResourceBundle) method. If there is a global resourceBundle set it will be merged with the resourceBundle provided by this builder method. The resourceBundle provided by this method will have a higher priority then the global one which means that if there are duplicate keys, the values of the global resourceBundle will be overwritten and the values of this resourceBundle will be used.
        Parameters:
        resourceBundle - the resource bundle that is used while loading the view.
        Returns:
        this instance of the builder step.

      • root

        public FluentViewLoader.FxmlViewStep<ViewType,ViewModelType> root(Object root)
        This param is used to define a JavaFX node that is used as the root element when loading the fxml file.
        This can be useful when creating custom controls with the fx:root element.
        Parameters:
        root - the root element that is used to load the fxml file.
        Returns:
        this instance of the builder step.

      • codeBehind

        public FluentViewLoader.FxmlViewStep<ViewType,ViewModelType> codeBehind(ViewType codeBehind)
        This param is used to define an existing instance of the codeBehind class that is used instead of creating a new one while loading.
        This can be useful when creating custom controls with the fx:root element.
        Parameters:
        codeBehind - the codeBehind instance that is used to load the fxml file.
        Returns:
        this instance of the builder step.

      • viewModel

        public FluentViewLoader.FxmlViewStep<ViewType,ViewModelType> viewModel(ViewModelType viewModel)
        This param is used to define an existing viewModel instance to be used when loading the view.
        A typical use case is when you like to have two or more views that are sharing the same viewModel.
        Parameters:
        viewModel - the viewModel instance that is used to load the fxml file.
        Returns:
        this instance of the builder step.

      • load

        The final step of the Fluent API. This method loads the view based on the given params.
        Returns:
        a view tuple containing the loaded view.
